Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.86,0:00:05.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Your newbie hasn't quit yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.32,0:00:07.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, he's hanging in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.11,0:00:08.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.35,0:00:12.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a good judge of character,\N regardless of what you may think.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.31,0:00:13.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.76,0:00:16.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone younger than Sakaki-kun quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.46,0:00:22.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's here. Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.42,0:00:25.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.80,0:00:27.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.76,0:00:30.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is it in our jurisdiction?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.20,0:00:32.05,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.30,0:00:34.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.11,0:00:41.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But my request to investigate\N the scene keeps getting rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.69,0:00:44.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And if you get us involved,\N that problem will go away?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.03,0:00:52.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's about right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.04,0:02:28.96,sign_6555_61_April_6th___Shin,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,400)}June 13th \NNocturnal Community Relations Section
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.99,0:02:29.00,Default - Top,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to investigate the north\N and south elevators at City Hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.30,0:02:32.38,Default - Top,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We got official permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.50,0:02:34.50,Ep_Title,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,550)}#5 "The Parallel World Elevator of \N the City Hall Observation Deck"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.38,0:02:34.91,Default - Top,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.91,0:02:37.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.56,0:02:40.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's an urban legend that's been going around!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.41,0:02:42.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Parallel World Elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.55,0:02:44.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You've at least heard of it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.80,0:02:47.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Um... No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.91,0:02:51.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, when you're in this line of work,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.24,0:02:53.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,you've gotta keep an ear to the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.55,0:02:56.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Search for it online. You'll find it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.48,0:02:59.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.00,0:03:01.84,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Someone posted to our occult message board
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.84,0:03:04.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,saying that somebody went up\N to the City Hall observation deck,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.55,0:03:06.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and ended up in another world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.79,0:03:07.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,"Our"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.74,0:03:09.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.41,0:03:20.42,sign_4566_35_I_went_up_the_ob,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I went up the observation deck in City Hall and ended up in another world lololol \N\N{\c&HC81A2A&}Anonymous, Lost in a Parallel Dimension \N{\c&H56434A&}Oh shit. No idea where I am. \N\N{\c&HC81A2A&}Anonymous, Lost in a Parallel Dimension\N {\c&H56434A&}I went up to the observation deck and everybody disappeared. It's just me. \N\N{\c&HC81A2A&}Anonymous, Lost in a Parallel Dimension \N{\u1\c&H82A584&}>>0002{\u0} {\c&H56434A&}Which observation deck? \N\N{\c&HC81A2A&}Anonymous, Lost in a Parallel Dimension \N{\u1\c&H82A584&}>>0003{\u0} {\c&H56434A&}City Hall. Tokyo. \N\N{\c&HC81A2A&}Anonymous, Lost in a Parallel Dimension
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.11,0:03:15.03,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The poster kept a running\N account of what was going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.03,0:03:17.41,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,before they simply stopped posting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.41,0:03:20.81,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The rumors say he probably went missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.81,0:03:24.16,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since then, small numbers\N of other people have appeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.16,0:03:26.40,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,saying the same thing happened to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.40,0:03:31.69,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Some were clearly trolling,\N but for the others, it's not so clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.34,0:03:35.19,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The number of rumors is increasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.60,0:03:39.69,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The police are looking for the missing people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.97,0:03:44.07,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But why are we sticking our noses in it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.71,0:03:49.20,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there's been something else happening...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.28,0:03:54.12,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,She disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.51,0:03:59.63,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,At first I thought she was a victim\N of the Parallel World Elevator, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.98,0:04:04.13,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,She's back?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.41,0:04:06.80,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,With no visible injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.80,0:04:11.02,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,She simply lost her memories\N of her time in the observatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.47,0:04:15.24,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,And there's several other similar reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.15,0:04:21.17,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Missing persons and missing memories, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.17,0:04:24.47,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Which means there're\Ntwo Anothers at City Hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.47,0:04:26.33,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.33,0:04:28.03,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to think about it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.33,0:04:32.21,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Sakaki-kun's just gone to meet\N with the girl and hear her story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.79,0:04:36.04,sign_6517_57_June_13th,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,400)}June 13th
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.21,0:04:34.87,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It seems they're acquainted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.01,0:04:40.73,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,So, I remember getting to\N the south observation deck,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.73,0:04:43.45,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,but the next thing I knew, I was at\N the north deck for some reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.45,0:04:45.35,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I was so shocked!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.23,0:04:48.05,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Anything else unusual?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.05,0:04:49.47,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.84,0:04:53.60,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Kyo-chan, you're not scared\N of the occult at all, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.01,0:04:57.56,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Has anyone you know\N experienced anything similar?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.55,0:05:03.16,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,A friend of mine once told me that \Nshe'd gotten into the north elevator
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.16,0:05:06.05,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,and ended up in some weird\N place where she saw a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.05,0:05:08.67,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Like in that urban legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.67,0:05:12.28,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,And your friend remembered this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.86,0:05:17.28,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Besides the fact that you lost your memories,\N nothing else happened, right, Aoi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.10,0:05:20.46,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I can't think of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.91,0:05:23.34,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Aoi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:27.01,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? You look so serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.01,0:05:29.97,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Did you make up with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.38,0:05:32.51,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Your boyfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.51,0:05:34.95,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.95,0:05:36.73,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.73,0:05:40.35,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,There's a new girl at work\N who I think is a good match for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.35,0:05:42.23,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,How about I throw a mixer?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.73,0:05:48.74,sign_6555_61_April_6th___Shin,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,400)}June 13th
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.57,0:05:46.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So, learn anything from Aoi-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.56,0:05:47.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Aoi-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.90,0:05:49.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A customer from when I was a host.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:52.05,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.05,0:05:54.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't get much in the way of clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.08,0:05:58.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There's one thing that bothered me, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.75,0:06:01.75,sign_8602_87_Let_s_break_up__,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let's break up...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.27,0:06:03.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She had a boyfriend\N she was thinking of marrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.19,0:06:07.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But just the other day, he broke up with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.81,0:06:13.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,However, when I met her, she didn't \Nseem at all bothered by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.51,0:06:16.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You don't think she just got over it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.59,0:06:17.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.93,0:06:20.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It was more like she'd forgotten it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.96,0:06:24.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So she lost her memories of being engaged?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.05,0:06:28.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She remembered her boyfriend, and the breakup.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.68,0:06:34.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But it was like she'd lost the memories\N of being depressed or the sadness she'd felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.28,0:06:35.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it felt to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.76,0:06:41.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, first, we need to examine the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.17,0:06:45.92,sign_6555_61_April_6th___Shin,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,June 13th\N Tokyo City Hall Building 1, First Floor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.73,0:06:48.61,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Theo?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.61,0:06:53.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No sign of any crests or spells...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.16,0:06:58.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So it's not likely artificial, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.22,0:06:59.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Artificial?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.18,0:07:03.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Like incorporating magic into the elevator\N itself into make into some kind of device.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.23,0:07:04.44,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.83,0:07:08.39,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,For example, if a believer in\N a god, or what we call an Another,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.39,0:07:13.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,created a magical gate\N to offer their deity sacrifices.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.24,0:07:16.67,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The victims would have no idea what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.67,0:07:19.86,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,as they passed through the gate\N and right to the Another's presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.42,0:07:26.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The data we have made it seem like it happens
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.34,0:07:29.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,when you leave the elevator\N to go into the observation deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.98,0:07:31.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So, we should go up?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.25,0:07:35.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Theo, head up to the south\N deck and take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.05,0:07:38.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako and I will take\N a look at the north deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.52,0:07:39.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.01,0:07:44.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Pray for me, so I don't\N end up in a parallel world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.15,0:07:48.38,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's not funny...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.50,0:07:51.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.04,0:07:53.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.12,0:07:55.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Up it is, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.78,0:07:56.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.54,0:08:01.54,date,,0000,0000,0000,,June 14th
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.57,0:08:08.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Um,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.11,0:08:12.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,the missing persons and missing\N memories cases are occurring at random
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.19,0:08:15.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,in both the north and south elevators, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.91,0:08:19.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We don't know what makes them happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.79,0:08:21.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Why would someone do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.76,0:08:22.86,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.86,0:08:26.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The goals of the Anothers\N are beyond our comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.07,0:08:30.69,date,,0000,0000,0000,,June 14th
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.30,0:08:33.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.93,0:08:47.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the Parallel World?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.21,0:08:50.36,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.70,0:08:55.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Give what you have to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.80,0:08:57.80,sign_12871_133_Shinjuku_Ward,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjuku Ward
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.31,0:09:00.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.27,0:09:07.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.21,0:09:09.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Arata, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.17,0:09:17.08,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Did they end up going to that other world?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.08,0:09:18.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.41,0:09:27.04,date,,0000,0000,0000,,June 14th
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.37,0:09:29.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.67,0:09:30.42,date - Copy,,0000,0000,0000,,June 14th
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.57,0:09:37.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kyoichi! Arata!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.97,0:09:40.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.66,0:09:42.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They did?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.89,0:09:46.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Give them to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.40,0:09:52.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do you know what she's saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.07,0:09:53.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,"Give them to me."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.93,0:09:55.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Give what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.10,0:09:56.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.16,0:09:58.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.44,0:10:04.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What you have...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.03,0:10:06.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.25,0:10:08.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! Did I make a mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.04,0:10:10.24,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.24,0:10:11.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.41,0:10:15.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You have nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.68,0:10:17.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You've got nothing to do with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:20.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You made contact with\N this human at the entrance
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.32,0:10:22.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and came with him, it feels like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.53,0:10:23.93,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Contact at the entrance?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.49,0:10:27.35,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Was it then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.79,0:10:29.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,How many times has this happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.89,0:10:33.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe when you prioritize efficiency,\N you become less accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.41,0:10:36.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Efficiency? Accurate?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.30,0:10:38.86,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You're human, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.86,0:10:41.23,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But you understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.23,0:10:42.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.76,0:10:46.37,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking with a human! How wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.13,0:10:50.95,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Since you're here, I'd like to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.95,0:10:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Talk to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.39,0:10:53.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.89,0:10:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.03,0:10:56.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Miyako!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.47,0:11:00.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.69,0:11:03.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.96,0:11:07.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sakaki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.15,0:11:12.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kyoichi! Kyoichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.50,0:11:13.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kyoichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.47,0:11:18.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.49,0:11:19.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Arata?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.77,0:11:20.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She got him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.98,0:11:23.94,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She controls that space.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.94,0:11:27.38,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We went to another world, and I was sent back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.60,0:11:31.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I made a mistake...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.71,0:11:36.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sakaki-san? No...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.70,0:11:40.98,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,He was in the way, so I got rid of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.02,0:11:43.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is he okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.87,0:11:45.39,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I just sent him back outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.02,0:11:48.60,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can talk, can't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.60,0:11:51.39,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.65,0:11:53.23,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.23,0:11:55.86,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.86,0:11:56.65,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.29,0:12:00.40,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gathering the things\N that escaped from this box.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.90,0:12:05.28,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So she has nothing to do with the\N disappearances and the missing memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.24,0:12:11.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I use that device to tell me who has\N what I'm looking for and who doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.58,0:12:15.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Only those who have it are sent to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.11,0:12:19.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But when I set it to send me more\N people, it started making mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.66,0:12:23.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It started sending people who \Nonly had something similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.29,0:12:25.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Similar?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.80,0:12:27.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Similar to what you're looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.89,0:12:34.12,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The man you were with held a tremendous \Nsense of loss, and that tripped the device.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.24,0:12:37.90,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking for a sense of loss, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.90,0:12:40.32,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But of a slightly different sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.32,0:12:43.03,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A sense of loss? Sakaki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.48,0:12:46.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Any luck, Theo?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.84,0:12:50.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I kept trying,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.09,0:12:55.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,which means there needs to be some\N condition met that we don't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.02,0:12:56.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.53,0:12:58.44,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.67,0:13:01.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.58,0:13:02.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.45,0:13:07.94,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This box once contained many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.94,0:13:11.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Bad things. Sad feelings. Diseases and crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.24,0:13:13.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,All sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.59,0:13:16.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So I was told not to open it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.72,0:13:22.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But when I cracked it open\N just a bit, they all flew off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.41,0:13:23.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It was my mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.88,0:13:27.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Some of the box's contents,\N feelings of loss in love,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.65,0:13:30.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,fell here in Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.85,0:13:33.95,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you collecting lost\N loves in a City Hall elevator?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.75,0:13:35.71,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,City Hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.19,0:13:39.56,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anything about human buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.56,0:13:44.21,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I make paths to this place in all\N the places that meet my needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.53,0:13:49.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then there are other elevators\N in Asia that lead here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.86,0:13:54.35,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Here, just wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.78,0:13:58.64,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I hope this one isn't a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.65,0:14:04.99,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Good. This one is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.13,0:14:10.27,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking your feelings of lost love.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.87,0:14:30.89,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.62,0:14:33.89,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you may return.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.64,0:14:36.71,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You're just going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.80,0:14:41.29,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Just as you came.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.88,0:14:49.09,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,When you wake up,\N you'll be where you wish to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.37,0:14:57.08,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,That girl had a pretty big stock.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.08,0:14:59.51,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It may be time to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.53,0:15:03.55,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I've almost recovered enough lost love,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.55,0:15:07.44,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,so next I'm going to Europe\N to recover jealousy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.44,0:15:10.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean you're leaving City Hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.39,0:15:19.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, it triggers when\N you leave the elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.77,0:15:21.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.46,0:15:23.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're our leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.03,0:15:28.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I need to bring back Miyako...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.63,0:15:32.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call Reiji-kun and come up with a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.76,0:15:35.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We won't get anywhere at this rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.99,0:15:38.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Reiji-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.75,0:15:40.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We've got problems...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.78,0:15:41.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.05,0:15:43.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kyoichi! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.81,0:15:47.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's really so much more\N wonderful when it's filled.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.98,0:15:54.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But this box was essentially my dowry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:54.59,sign_22840_252_Izumi,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Izumi
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:54.59,sign_22840_253_When_are_you_tur,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,When are you turning on your phone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.87,0:15:54.59,Default - Top,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Izumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.59,0:15:58.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So it's weird that they'd\N tell me not to open it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.40,0:15:56.93,Default - Top,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can send messages!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.35,0:16:04.35,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,How does it make any sense for me \Nto not open my own dowry?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.81,0:16:07.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Can't take... any more...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.28,0:16:11.61,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm calling Reiji-kun\N regardless of what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.23,0:16:14.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I can call him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.32,0:16:18.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No way. The barrier probably blocks out voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.33,0:16:26.71,sign_23577_261_Theo,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Theo
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.33,0:16:26.71,sign_23577_262_I_m_hungry,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.33,0:16:26.71,sign_23577_263_Miyako_Arata_,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako Arata
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.33,0:16:26.71,sign_23577_264_Sakaki_san__are_,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sakaki-san, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.89,0:16:25.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.28,0:16:26.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't get through on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.48,0:16:30.11,Default,GU,0000,0000,0000,,The posts from the other world!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.11,0:16:31.55,Default,GU,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.55,0:16:33.84,Default,GU,0000,0000,0000,,That guy was posting on his\N phone from another world!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.84,0:16:39.10,sign_23829_270_What_s_your_stat,GU,0000,0000,0000,,What's your status?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.72,0:16:39.10,sign_23577_263_Miyako_Arata_,GU,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako Arata
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.72,0:16:39.10,sign_23577_264_Sakaki_san__are_,GU,0000,0000,0000,,Talking with the Another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:39.10,sign_23577_264_Sakaki_san__are_,GU,0000,0000,0000,,I don't seem to be in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.10,0:16:44.50,Default - Top,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You probably caught a glimpse of it,\N but the bad things in the box are...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.38,0:16:44.48,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,"She has nothing to do with the missing\N people or missing memories."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.48,0:16:44.98,sign_24084_278_What_s_your_situ,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,What's your situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.48,0:16:46.60,sign_24084_277_Nocturnal_Commun,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Nocturnal Community Relations Section (4)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.48,0:16:46.60,sign_24084_278_What_s_your_situ,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Talking with the Another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.48,0:16:46.60,sign_24084_278_What_s_your_situ,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't seem to be in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.48,0:16:46.60,sign_24084_278_What_s_your_situ,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,She has nothing to do with the missing \Npeople or missing memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.98,0:16:46.60,sign_24096_282_She_s_just_colle,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,She's just collecting feelings of lost love.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.91,0:16:48.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Feelings of lost love?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.45,0:16:49.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.65,0:16:52.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The lost memories are her doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.08,0:16:55.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The weird thing I felt when I talked to Aoi...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.43,0:16:59.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Her feelings of lost love were stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.37,0:17:04.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,An Another that steals emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.99,0:17:08.50,Default - Top,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,If they fly out of the box again,\N I have to gather them up...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.05,0:17:07.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.50,0:17:13.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,When you take their feelings of lost\N love, do you take their memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.82,0:17:15.47,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.47,0:17:17.14,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She says she doesn't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.01,0:17:21.89,sign_24912_294_She_says_she_doe,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She says she doesn't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.98,0:17:21.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She probably really doesn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.74,0:17:25.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She's not doing it deliberately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.35,0:17:29.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't care if someone\N finds her or sees her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.78,0:17:32.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's why she left my memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.78,0:17:36.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But if she's responsible\N for the missing memories,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.74,0:17:38.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,then is there another Another somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.66,0:17:40.83,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.92,0:17:43.83,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There are no missing people?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.16,0:17:49.21,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We were able to ID that message\N board poster and get a hold of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.21,0:17:52.09,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There was no missing\N person report filed on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.39,0:17:55.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They said they remembered going to City Hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.89,0:17:58.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,but had no memory of making the posts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.89,0:18:02.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I see where this case is going...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.61,0:18:08.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The person was believed to have gone missing\N because they stopped posting after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.12,0:18:13.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But if, like the ones who lost their memories,\N he forgot what happened in the other world,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.68,0:18:15.36,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,he wouldn't be able to keep posting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.08,0:18:18.87,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody went missing at all, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.82,0:18:25.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So the missing people and missing\N memories were all your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.90,0:18:31.08,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible for you to stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.61,0:18:33.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Stop what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.31,0:18:36.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for what you want with that elevator!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.36,0:18:38.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.62,0:18:40.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,People want to use that elevator to go places!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.85,0:18:42.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's not a problem for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.58,0:18:45.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No, not you. Other people!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.60,0:18:47.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I have to stop looking for what I want
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.33,0:18:50.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,because it's causing a problem for people?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.26,0:18:53.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There's no reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.85,0:19:00.17,Flashback_Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do if they\N demand your life in exchange?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.17,0:19:04.16,Flashback_Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You should learn more about\N the scary parts of Anothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.57,0:19:08.41,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Just because I can talk to them doesn't\N mean we understand each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.80,0:19:11.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Anothers and humans can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.81,0:19:15.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.18,0:19:17.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.81,0:19:19.55,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I see. What a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.03,0:19:24.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Come back again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.60,0:19:28.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make it so you can come\N here any time you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.21,0:19:31.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Um... One last thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.88,0:19:33.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.24,0:19:35.27,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Name?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.17,0:19:40.03,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Humans call me, "Pandora."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.54,0:19:42.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Pandora? Box...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.87,0:19:45.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Pandora's Box?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.38,0:19:49.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing more coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.87,0:19:52.37,sign_28553_339_She_s_just_colle,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She's just collecting feelings of lost love.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.87,0:19:52.37,sign_28553_340_She_says_she_doe,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She says she doesn't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.87,0:19:52.37,sign_28553_341_I_m_coming_back_,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.50,0:19:57.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.50,0:19:57.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Arata!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.62,0:20:00.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.28,0:20:02.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you okay? Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.90,0:20:06.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't make any promises with the\N Another, or take anything from them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.35,0:20:09.14,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, nothing like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.48,0:20:11.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.75,0:20:13.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.81,0:20:16.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I should've been more careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.11,0:20:19.36,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not true...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.07,0:20:24.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Arata's okay. So it all worked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.11,0:20:27.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're packing up for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.47,0:20:30.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let's write our report and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.04,0:20:32.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.61,0:20:40.05,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going right to sleep when I get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.05,0:20:42.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We should eat first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.48,0:20:43.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Miyako?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.49,0:20:45.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.19,0:20:48.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hello there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.35,0:20:50.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.30,0:20:51.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.54,0:20:54.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I read the report.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.52,0:20:57.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,One Another was responsible\N for both cases, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.69,0:20:59.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like a long night.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.33,0:21:04.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What good are the Ears of Sand?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.38,0:21:09.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I can talk to the Anothers,\N I couldn't resolve anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.00,0:21:15.99,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Our job isn't to find the big solutions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.09,0:21:22.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You came back safe, and the Another\N at City Hall is going to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.24,0:21:25.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The case is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.55,0:21:35.46,Default - Top,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Yokoyama-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.46,0:21:38.97,Default - Top,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The matter at City Hall's been resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.12,0:21:44.38,Default - Top,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sure. I can pay you back\N by taking you out to eat...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.40,0:21:45.93,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There's one thing I couldn't put in the report.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.80,0:21:51.74,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That Sakaki-san's sense of loss\N is what brought us to Pandora.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:57.06,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sakaki-san's sense of tremendous loss...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.87,0:21:59.92,sign_31550_377_Unsolved_Missing,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,1)}Unsolved Missing Girl Cases in Tokyo
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.06,0:21:58.15,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What could it be?
